[ANALYSIS]
The experiment "transformer_20260421_175928_run_02" using a Transformer architecture with the DistilBERT model crashed due to an indexing error in the MPS (Metal Performance Shaders) backend of PyTorch. The specific error indicates that there was an attempt to access an index out of bounds, which suggests a mismatch between expected tensor dimensions and actual data provided during the embedding bag operation. Despite the crash, no metrics were recorded, and the repair plan did not suggest any changes to the configuration.

For the next run, it is crucial to ensure compatibility between the model architecture and the MPS backend by verifying that all operations are correctly implemented for this hardware acceleration. Additionally, checking the data preprocessing steps to confirm that tensor dimensions match the expected input sizes could prevent similar indexing errors. Adjusting the batch size or modifying the model configuration might also help in stabilizing the training process.